Reverse Vowels of a String — what the question really means

At first glance:

“Reverse vowels of a string.”

Sounds similar to reversing the whole string, but it’s not.

What they want is:

Only vowels change position

All other characters stay exactly where they are

The order of vowels is reversed

Input : "hello"
Output: "holle"





def reverse_vowels(str)
  vowels = Set.new(%w[a e i o u A E I O U])
  ###  vowels = Set.new(['a','i','e','o','u','A','I','E','O','U'])

  left = 0
  right = str.length - 1

  while left < right
    if !vowels.include?(str[left])
      left += 1
    elsif !vowels.include?(str[right])
      right -= 1
    else
      str[left], str[right] = str[right], str[left]
      left += 1
      right -= 1
    end
  end

  str
end

puts reverse_vowels("hello")      # => "holle"
puts reverse_vowels("hEllO")      # => "hOllE"
puts reverse_vowels("leetcode")   # => "leotceed"
